Honestly rather mediocre for the price. Appetizers are good but astonishingly expensive for the amount of food you get. Empenadas were enjoyable but a bit dry, and we were never brought any sauce or salsa. I got the combination special, and the steak and chicken actually were excellent, although the sides were somewhat bland. However, both of my friends got the churrasco, and it was terribly overcooked. One ordered it medium, the other medium rare, and both came cooked all the way through, literally well done. Furthermore, the service was super slow the whole time, they seemed to be understaffed on a Saturday somehow. All in all it wasn't a horrible experience. If we had simply ordered some other things and the service had been better, this would have been a glowing review, but unfortunately there were some serious and notable issues with our meal for the price.
